<p>The global digital agency market reached $460 billion in 2024 and is projected to exceed $600 billion by 2028. The agencies winning that growing spend are not the cheapest. They are the most clearly positioned.</p>
<p>Each model serves a different purpose. Monthly retainers work best for long-term relationships where consistent output drives compounding results. Hourly billing suits defined consulting engagements. Project-based pricing works when the scope is clearly bounded. Value-based models are the most profitable but require the most trust.</p>
<p>The agencies that earn the most pick one primary model and use the others selectively.</p>
